urlhtml: Beatles' Please Please Me album cover
title: Beatles' Please Please Me album cover
description: EMI House at 20 Manchester Square, Marylebone, is the location of the staircase seen on the cover of the Beatles' 1963 album Please Please Me, and the 1973 compilations,  the Red Album and the Blue Album. All three album covers were shot by Angus McBean, the Please Please Me and Red Album images were from the same 1963 session, while the Blue Album was taken in 1969.

title: The London Oyster House
description:
Oysters used to be the fast food of the day in the early 20th centuary and a chain of Oyster Houses operated across the capital with the familiar Lighthouse Dome on top.  Sadly today this seems to be the last surviving example of these historic buildings, last used to operate as a fish and chip shop.

See:  http://www.urban75.org/london/oyster-bar-kings-cross.html for more information

title: The Grenadier Pub
description:
This pub is difficult to find, you won't see many tourists in here. This building was used by the Duke of Wellington's Grenadier Guards as a mess.  The walls are cluttered with military memorabilia. This is in an exclusive area of London and considered a gentleman's club, so avoid tourist dress (shorts, t-shirts, etc.) They have a good selection of food, a bit pricey as pub food goes. The specialty is a Bloody Mary made from a secret recipe.
This pub boasts the oldest pewter bar and has a reputation of being the most haunted pub in London.
 
020 7235 3074
http://www.taylor-walker.co.uk/pub/grenadier-belgrave-square/c0800
http://www.fancyapint.com/Pub/london/grenadier/384

title: Talbots
description:
Talbots (NYSE: TLB) is a Massachusetts clothing retailer established in 1947. The store specializes in clothing, shoes, and accessories.

Talbots offers petite sizes, proportioned for shorter women, and petite-woman sizes for shorter women who are not necessarily skinny.

In 2004, Talbots introduced a men's line.

Talbot's classic style, once very conservative, has changed to include bright colors, unusual designs as a new classic for the modern consumer.

The first store was located in Hingham, Massachusetts. During the following year, they established a direct mail service which would originate their catalog service. In 1973, General Mills acquired Talbots. Talbots was listed on the New York Stock Exchange beginning in 1993.

At the end of 2005, there were 1,083 stores in the United States, Canada, and the UK, as well as 4 stores in Japan.

urlhtml: The John Snow Pub (corner of Lexington and Brewer St's Soho)
title: The John Snow Pub (corner of Lexington and Brewer St's Soho)
description: The John Snow is named after the famed Epidemologist Who first discovered that Cholera was transmitted through water. The Original tap to the Brewer St Pump, is still situated in a locked cabinet in the upstairs bar. The site shown as the pump monument is no more than 200 yards away and is marked by a blue curbstone, to the right side of the Brewer st entrance to the pub (another Sam Smiths)
